```

### 14.7 Message Reuse

Approved messages must be stored within the system and made available for reuse.

**Reuse Rules:**

- Employees must be able to select previously approved templates
- Selected templates auto-populate with case-specific data
- Custom modifications require Marketing re-approval
- Template usage is tracked for audit purposes

### 14.8 Customer Document Upload

When documentation is requested, the system must allow the customer to upload documents through digital channels.

**Supported Upload Channels:**

| Channel | Description | Priority |
|---------|-------------|----------|
| QIB Mobile Banking | Primary digital channel | High |
| QIB Lite | Lite mobile application | High |
| Microsite | Dedicated upload portal | Medium |
| Branch FLOW System | In-branch assisted upload | Medium |

**Mobile App Popup Notification:**

When the customer logs into the mobile application, a **popup notification** must appear displaying the request:

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ⚠️ Action Required                    │
│                                        │
│  Additional KYC information is         │
│  required. Please upload the           │
│  requested documents.                  │
│                                        │
│  Reference: EDD-2024-001234            │
│                                        │
│  [View Details]    [Upload Now]        │
└────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 14.9 Temporary Upload Window

Document upload must remain active until:

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Requested documents submitted | Upload window closes |
| Documents reviewed and approved | Notification removed |
| EDD case closed | All notifications cleared |
| SLA deadline exceeded | Escalation triggered |

Once documents are approved, the notification must be automatically removed from all channels.

### 14.10 Multi-Channel Notification Delivery

Customer notifications must be delivered across multiple channels.

**Supported Delivery Channels:**

| Channel | Type | Delivery Method |
|---------|------|-----------------|
| SMS | Push | SMS Gateway |
| Mobile App Notification | Push | Firebase/APNs |
| Email | Push | Email Gateway |
| QIB Lite App | Push | In-app notification |
| Microsite | Pull | Portal banner |
| ATM Interface | Pull | Screen message |
| Branch FLOW System | Pull | Employee alert |
| Call Center System | Pull | CRM integration |

When a customer interacts with any of these channels, the system must display the notification.

### 14.11 Branch and Call Center Visibility

When a customer visits a branch or calls the contact center, the system must display the active notification.

**Employee View Requirements:**

| Information | Display |
|-------------|---------|
| Notification text | Full message content |
| Required documents | Document checklist |
| EDD case reference | Case ID and status |
| Upload status | Documents received/pending |
| SLA countdown | Days remaining |

This allows employees to assist the customer with document submission.

### 14.12 Notification Removal

Notifications must automatically disappear once:

| Event | System Action |
|-------|---------------|
| Required documents uploaded | Mark as "Pending Review" |
| Documents approved by reviewer | Remove notification |
| Case closed | Clear all related notifications |

### 14.13 Marketing Governance

The **Marketing Department** must have full control over message templates.

**Marketing Responsibilities:**

| Responsibility | Description |
|----------------|-------------|
| Edit notification texts | Modify template content |
| Approve message templates | Maker-Checker approval |
| Define delivery channels | Select channels per template |
| Ensure communication consistency | Brand and tone guidelines |
| Archive old templates | Version control |

Marketing must operate under **Maker and Checker approval** for all changes.

### 14.14 Channel Trigger Control

The EDD system must trigger notifications through the bank's **central communication gateway**.

**Integration Points:**

| Gateway | Protocol | Purpose |
|---------|----------|---------|
| SMS Gateway | REST API | SMS delivery |
| Email Gateway | SMTP/API | Email delivery |
| Mobile Push | Firebase/APNs | App notifications |
| Internal ESB | SOAP/REST | Banking channel sync |

### 14.15 Audit and Compliance

All notifications must be recorded in the audit trail.

**Logged Information:**

| Event | Logged Data |
|-------|-------------|
| Notification creation | Date, user, template, channel |
| Notification approval | Approver, timestamp, comments |
| Message content | Full text, variables used |
| Delivery status | Channel, delivery time, status |
| Document upload | Upload date, file details |
| Document approval | Reviewer, approval date |

