## 29. Case Collaboration and Internal Communication

### 29.1 Overview

The EDD system must support an internal collaboration feature that allows employees to communicate within the context of an EDD case.

This feature enables case participants to exchange messages, share insights, and collaborate on case analysis without leaving the system.

All conversations must be recorded and stored as part of the EDD case history.

### 29.2 Case Chat Functionality

Each EDD case must include a **case chat interface** that allows employees to communicate within the case.

**Required Capabilities:**

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Internal chat | Employees can send messages within the case |
| Participant tagging | Users can tag other employees using @mention |
| Add participants | Additional users may be invited to the case discussion |
| File attachments | Documents may be attached to chat messages |
| Message history | All messages must be preserved permanently |
| Read receipts | System tracks message read status |
| Reply threading | Users can reply to specific messages |

### 29.3 Chat Workflow

Employees must be able to initiate discussions directly within the EDD case.

**Example Workflow:**

```
┌────────────────────┐
│   CDD Officer      │
│   Opens Chat       │
└─────────┬──────────┘
          │
          ↓
┌────────────────────┐
│ Sends Message      │
│ Tags @BusinessUser │
└─────────┬──────────┘
          │
          ↓
┌────────────────────┐
│ Business User      │
│ Receives Alert     │
└─────────┬──────────┘
          │
          ↓
┌────────────────────┐
│ Business Response  │
│ Provides Info      │
└─────────┬──────────┘
          │
          ↓
┌────────────────────┐
│ Case Updated       │
│ Chat Archived      │
└────────────────────┘
```

All messages must remain permanently attached to the EDD case.

### 29.4 Participant Management

Users must be able to add additional participants to the chat.

**Eligible Participants:**

| Participant Type | Role |
|-----------------|------|
| Business Users | Relationship Managers, Business Makers/Checkers |
| Sector Supervisors | Department heads with case oversight |
| CDD Operations | EDD case processors |
| Compliance Officers | For escalated cases |
| Call Center Supervisors | For customer contact coordination |
| IT Support | For technical issues |

The system must log all participants in the case collaboration section with:
- Participant name
- Employee ID
- Date/time joined
- Invited by (employee ID)

### 29.5 Message Archiving

All chat messages must be archived as part of the case documentation.

**Stored Information:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Message ID | Unique identifier (UUID) |
| Case ID | EDD case reference |
| Sender Name | Employee full name |
| Employee ID | Staff number |
| Department | Department name |
| Job Title | Official position |
| Timestamp | Date and time (with timezone) |
| Message Content | Full text message |
| Attachments | List of attached files |
| Tagged Users | List of mentioned employees |
| Parent Message ID | For reply threading |

**Retention Policy:**
- All chat messages retained for **7 years minimum**
- Messages cannot be deleted or edited after sending
- Export capability for audit/regulatory requests

### 29.6 Case Attachment Storage

Files shared in chat must be stored as **EDD case attachments**.

**Supported Attachments:**

| Type | Formats | Max Size |
|------|---------|----------|
| Screenshots | PNG, JPG, GIF | 10MB |
| Documents | PDF, DOC, DOCX, XLS, XLSX | 25MB |
| Investigation Notes | PDF, TXT | 10MB |
| Regulatory References | PDF | 25MB |

**Storage Requirements:**
- Files must be stored in the **bank's DMS system (FileNet)**
- Linked to the EDD case with unique document ID
- Version control for replaced documents
- Automatic virus scanning before storage

