## 35. Data Governance & Data Ownership

### 35.1 Overview

This section defines the data governance framework for the EDD Case Management System, ensuring data quality, ownership accountability, and regulatory compliance.

Data governance is critical for:
- Regulatory compliance (QCB, FATF, AML requirements)
- Data quality assurance
- Clear accountability
- Audit readiness
- Operational efficiency

### 35.2 Data Ownership Matrix

Each data element in the EDD system has a designated owner responsible for data quality and accuracy.

**System Data Ownership:**

| Data Domain | Data Owner | Data Steward | System of Record |
|-------------|------------|--------------|------------------|
| Customer Master Data | Head of Operations | CDD Manager | T24 |
| Risk Classification | Chief Risk Officer | Risk Manager | CRP Engine |
| EDD Case Data | Head of Operations | EDD Supervisor | FLOW |
| KYC Documents | Head of Operations | CDD Manager | DMS |
| Transaction Data | Head of IT | Data Manager | T24 |
| Employee Data | Head of HR | HR Manager | HR System |
| Audit Data | Chief Audit Officer | Audit Manager | FLOW |
| Notification Data | Head of Marketing | Marketing Manager | Notification Gateway |

### 35.3 Data Classification

All data in the EDD system must be classified according to sensitivity.

**Data Classification Levels:**

| Classification | Description | Examples | Handling Requirements |
|----------------|-------------|----------|----------------------|
| Public | Non-sensitive data | Case status codes | Standard controls |
| Internal | Business operational data | Case statistics | Internal access only |
| Confidential | Sensitive business data | Customer names | Need-to-know access |
| Restricted | High-sensitivity data | QID, Financial data | Encryption required |
| Highly Restricted | PII/Critical data | Risk scores, PEP status | Maximum protection |

**Data Element Classification:**

| Data Element | Classification | Encryption | Masking |
|-------------|----------------|------------|---------|
| Customer RIM | Confidential | At rest | Display last 4 |
| Customer Name | Confidential | At rest | Partial |
| QID Number | Restricted | At rest + transit | Full mask except last 4 |
| Mobile Number | Confidential | At rest | Partial |
| Risk Score | Highly Restricted | At rest + transit | Role-based |
| PEP Status | Highly Restricted | At rest + transit | Role-based |
| Financial Data | Restricted | At rest + transit | Role-based |
| Case Comments | Internal | At rest | None |

### 35.4 Data Quality Standards

The EDD system must maintain high data quality standards.

**Data Quality Dimensions:**

| Dimension | Definition | Target | Measurement |
|-----------|------------|--------|-------------|
| Accuracy | Data matches reality | 99.5% | Monthly audit |
| Completeness | All required fields populated | 99% | System validation |
| Consistency | Same data across systems | 99% | Reconciliation |
| Timeliness | Data available when needed | Real-time | SLA monitoring |
| Validity | Data conforms to rules | 100% | Business rules |
| Uniqueness | No duplicate records | 100% | Deduplication |

**Data Quality Controls:**

| Control | Implementation | Frequency |
|---------|----------------|-----------|
| Field Validation | Business rules at entry | Real-time |
| Cross-system Reconciliation | T24 vs FLOW comparison | Daily |
| Duplicate Detection | Matching algorithm | On creation |
| Data Completeness Check | Mandatory field validation | Real-time |
| Referential Integrity | Foreign key validation | Real-time |
| Historical Data Audit | Data lineage review | Monthly |

