## 36. Customer Identity Re-Verification (Liveness Verification)

### 36.1 Overview

As part of the Enhanced Due Diligence (EDD) process, the system must support **customer identity re-verification** when additional identity confirmation is required.

The verification may be performed through three methods:

| Method | Channel | Use Case |
|--------|---------|----------|
| Live Selfie Capture | Mobile Banking / QIB Lite / Microsite | Digital verification |
| Branch Verification | Physical Branch Visit | In-person verification |
| Video Verification | Video Call with Bank Employee | Remote assisted verification |

The verification result must be recorded and linked to the EDD case.

### 36.2 Trigger Conditions

Identity verification may be triggered in the following scenarios:

| Scenario | Trigger Type | Priority |
|----------|--------------|----------|
| Customer classified as High Risk | Automatic | High |
| KYC data inconsistency detected | Automatic | High |
| AML indicator requiring identity confirmation | Automatic | Critical |
| Customer account flagged for EDD review | Automatic | Medium |
| Suspected fraudulent activity | Manual (Compliance) | Critical |
| Document authenticity concerns | Manual (CDD) | High |
| Long-term dormant account reactivation | Automatic | Medium |
| Significant change in transaction patterns | Automatic | High |

### 36.3 Digital Selfie Verification

When digital verification is selected, the system must send a notification to the customer requesting a **live selfie verification**.

**Notification Channels:**

| Channel | Notification Type | User Experience |
|---------|-------------------|-----------------|
| Mobile Banking | Push Notification + In-App Banner | Popup on login |
| QIB Lite | Push Notification + In-App Banner | Popup on login |
| Microsite | Email with Secure Link | Landing page with camera |
