### 38.10 Three-Layer Regulatory Control

This Dynamic Eligibility Validation adds **three critical regulatory control layers** to the EDD system:

**Layer 1: Continuous Risk Classification Verification**
- Real-time validation against T24 and CRP
- Automatic workflow pause if risk changes
- Prevents unnecessary EDD on non-high-risk customers

**Layer 2: Active Relationship Verification**
- Confirms customer still has bank relationship
- Checks account status before any action
- Prevents actions on closed/inactive relationships

**Layer 3: Compliance-Gated Case Closure**
- No automatic closure for exclusion cases
- Mandatory Compliance approval
- Full audit trail for regulators

**Regulatory Alignment:**
| Requirement | QCB Guideline | Implementation |
|-------------|---------------|----------------|
| Risk-Based Approach | Article 4.2 | Layer 1 - Risk verification |
| Customer Due Diligence | Article 5.1 | Layer 2 - Relationship verification |
| Compliance Oversight | Article 8.3 | Layer 3 - Approval workflow |
| Audit Trail | Article 10.1 | Full validation logging |

